*** Soo when comes to S - single response principle ***
1. a class should have only one reason to change

2. the INvoice class is the combination of all different functions,
soo there might be a chances we need to modify the different methods based on the situations.

3. soo we have came up with a plan such a way that dividing each functionalities into small small pieces and keep that as a class
this will leads to clear understanding of functionalities, maintainability, and easy to modify without distrubing other functionalities
and follows the rules of solid principles.

- Easy to maintain
- Avoid Duplicates
- Easy to understand
- Flexible Software
- Reduce Complexity

if something need to be changed in printRules class that will not effect to others.
